  "disabilityGapEduIjmTitle": "IJM vs DI: what's the difference?",
  "disabilityGapEduIjmBody": "The IJM (daily sickness benefit) is an insurance covering 80% of your salary for max. 720 days in case of illness. The employer is not required to subscribe, but many do through collective insurance. Without IJM, after the legal salary continuation period, you receive nothing until a potential DI pension.",
